                                [spacer.gif]
   [welcome.gif]
   The internet plays a vital role in helping citizens become more
   involved with local and national issues. Through the world wide web,
   people can follow important debates on proposed legislation and let
   their representatives know their opinions.
   In my Georgia and Washington, D.C. offices, we use the internet to
   listen to your concerns as well as to keep you abreast of what I am
   doing to serve Georgia citizens.
   I am delighted that you have taken this opportunity to learn about my
   Senate activities and the offices, services, and information available
   to you. Thanks for stopping by, and I hope you find the information
   useful.
   Let me know what you think!
                                [spacer.gif]
   [divline.gif]
   [spacer.gif]
   [terrorism.gif]
   [spacer.gif]
   [f18b.gif]
   In the months since the horrific attacks against America on September
   11th, we as a nation have unified behind our President, committed to
   bringing the terrorists to justice and ending the epidemic of fear
   around the globe. We continue to stand united as we pray for the safety
   of our men and women in uniform, work to make our own country as secure
   as possible and mourn those who fell.
   [spacer.gif]

                                          A statement from Senator Cleland

